Author: Sunopsis Version: 4.0 Last Update : DEC-2004
Description : - Integration Knowledge Module for DB2 400 - Integrates data in a DB2/400 target table in incremental update mode. - Inexistent rows are inserted; already existing rows are updated. - Data can be controlled. Invalid data is isolated in the Error Table and can be recycled. - When using this module with a journalized source table, it is possible to synchronize deletions.
Restrictions : - Comparison of data is made using the Update Key defined in the interface. It has to be set. - To use this IKM, the temporary (C$, I$...) and target tables should be stored in AS400 collections (or AS400 journalized libraries), otherwise, an SQL7008 message will be signalled (refer to the IBM DB2/400 documentation for details concerning SQLCode 7008). - The FLOW_CONTROL and STATIC_CONTROL options call the Check Knowledge Module to isolate invalid data (if no CKM is set, an error occurs). Both options must be set to NO in the case when an Integration Interface populates a TEMPORARY target datastore.
Automatically attempts to insert data into the Target Datastore of the Interface.
Identifies and updates rows of the Target Datastore depending on the value of the UPDATE_KEY columns of the target datastore records.
Check this option to synchronize journalized deletions. This option will take effect only if one source table is journalized in your interface
Uncheck this option if you do not want to perform a flow control
Check this option to recycle data rejected from a previous control.
Check this option to control the target table after having inserted or updated target data.
Check this option if you want to delete all the rows of the target datastore.
Check this option if you want to create the target table
Uncheck this option if you want to keep the integration table in the work area after the execution. Useful for debugging
Set this option to NO if you wish to retain temporary objects (tables, files and scripts) after integration. Useful for debugging.

delete from <%=snpRef.getTable("L","TARG_NAME","A")%> where exists ( select 'X' from <%=snpRef.getTable("L","INT_NAME","A")%> <%=snpRef.getInfo("DEST_TAB_ALIAS_WORD")%> I where <%=snpRef.getColList("", snpRef.getTable("L","TARG_NAME","A") + ".[COL_NAME]\t= I.[COL_NAME]", "\n\t\tand \t", "", "UK")%> and IND_UPDATE = 'D' )

insert into <%=snpRef.getTable("L","INT_NAME","A")%> ( <%=snpRef.getColList("", "[COL_NAME]", ",
	", "", "(((INS or UPD) and !TRG) and REW)")%> ) select <%=snpRef.getColList("", "[COL_NAME]", ",
	", "", "(((INS or UPD) and !TRG) and REW)")%> from <%=snpRef.getTable("L","ERR_NAME", "W")%> <%=snpRef.getInfo("DEST_TAB_ALIAS_WORD")%> E where not exists ( select 'X' from <%=snpRef.getTable("L","INT_NAME","W")%> <%=snpRef.getInfo("DEST_TAB_ALIAS_WORD")%> T where <%=snpRef.getColList("", "T.[COL_NAME]	= E.[COL_NAME]", "
		and	", "", "UK")%> ) and E.ORIGIN = '<%=snpRef.getInfo("CT_ORIGIN")%>' and E.ERR_TYPE = '<%=snpRef.getInfo("CT_ERR_TYPE")%>'

<% if ("C".equals(snpRef.getJrnInfo( "JRN_METHOD"))) { %> /* Consistant journalization detected. */ /* Lock should be done by a specific step in a package */ <% } else { %> update <%=snpRef.getTable( "L" , "JRN_NAME" , "A" )%> set JRN_CONSUMED = '1' where (1=1) <%=snpRef.getJrnFilter()%> <% } %>

insert into <%=snpRef.getTable("L","INT_NAME","A")%> ( <%=snpRef.getColList("", "[COL_NAME]", ",\n\t", ",", "(((INS or UPD) and !TRG) and REW)")%> IND_UPDATE ) select <%=snpRef.getPop("DISTINCT_ROWS")%> <%=snpRef.getColList("", "[EXPRESSION]", ",\n\t", ",", "(((INS or UPD) and !TRG) and REW)")%> <% if (snpRef.getPop("HAS_JRN").equals("0")) { %> 'I' IND_UPDATE <%} else {%> JRN_FLAG <%}%> from <%=snpRef.getFrom()%> where (1=1) <%=snpRef.getJoin()%> <%=snpRef.getFilter()%> <%=snpRef.getJrnFilter()%> <%=snpRef.getGrpBy()%> <%=snpRef.getHaving()%>

<% if ("C".equals(snpRef.getJrnInfo( "JRN_METHOD"))) { %> /* Consistant journalization detected. */ /* Lock should be done by a specific step in a package */ <% } else { %> delete from <%=snpRef.getTable("L","JRN_NAME","A")%> where JRN_CONSUMED = '1' <%=snpRef.getJrnFilter()%> <% } %>

insert into <%=snpRef.getTable("L","TARG_NAME","A")%> ( <%=snpRef.getColList("", "[COL_NAME]", ",
	", "", "((INS and !TRG) and REW)")%> <%=snpRef.getColList(",","[COL_NAME]", ",
	" , "", "((INS and TRG) and REW)")%> ) select <%=snpRef.getColList("", "[COL_NAME]", ",
	", "", "((INS and !TRG) and REW)")%> <%=snpRef.getColList(",","[EXPRESSION]", ",
	" , "", "((INS and TRG) and REW)")%> from <%=snpRef.getTable("L","INT_NAME","A")%> where IND_UPDATE = 'I'

update <%=snpRef.getTable("L", "TARG_NAME", "A")%> T set ( <%=snpRef.getColList("","[COL_NAME]", ",
	" , "", "(((UPD and !TRG) and !UK) and REW)")%> <%=snpRef.getColList(",","[COL_NAME]", ",
	" , "", "(((UPD and TRG) and !UK) and REW)")%> ) = ( select <%=snpRef.getColList("","[COL_NAME]", ",
			" , "", "(((UPD and !TRG) and !UK) and REW)")%> <%=snpRef.getColList(",","[EXPRESSION]", ",
			" , "", "(((UPD and TRG) and !UK) and REW)")%> from <%=snpRef.getTable("L", "INT_NAME", "A")%> S where (<%=snpRef.getColList("","T.[COL_NAME]	= S.[COL_NAME]", "
		and	", "", "UK") %>) and S.IND_UPDATE = 'U' ) where exists ( select 'X' from <%=snpRef.getTable("L", "INT_NAME", "A")%> I where <%=snpRef.getColList("","T.[COL_NAME]	= I.[COL_NAME]", "
		and	", "", "UK") %> and I.IND_UPDATE = 'U' )

update <%=snpRef.getTable("L", "INT_NAME", "A")%> S set IND_UPDATE = 'N' where exists ( select 'X' from <%=snpRef.getTable("L", "TARG_NAME", "A")%> T where <%=snpRef.getColList("","T.[COL_NAME]\t= S.[COL_NAME]", "\n\t\tand\t", "", "UK")%> <%=snpRef.getColList("and\t","((T.[COL_NAME] = S.[COL_NAME]) Or (T.[COL_NAME] IS NULL and S.[COL_NAME] IS NULL))", " \n\t\tand\t", "", "((UPD and !TRG) and !UK)")%> )

update <%=snpRef.getTable("L", "INT_NAME", "A")%> S set IND_UPDATE = 'U' where exists ( select 'X' from <%=snpRef.getTable("L", "TARG_NAME", "A")%> T where <%=snpRef.getColList("","T.[COL_NAME]\t= S.[COL_NAME]", "\n\t\tand\t", "", "UK")%> )
Create Unique Index on flow table
